AB  - This paper proposes an integral sliding mode control (ISMC) framework with three-dimensional (3D) guidance mapping for heterogeneous underactuated surface vessel (USV)-unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) system. Specifically, the system dynamics are modeled with external disturbances, model uncertainty, and input delays, while a graph-theoretic communication topology is adopted to enable distributed kinematic coordination between USV and UAV. Moreover, the 3D guidance mapping strategy incorporates marine-aerial spatial constraints into leader-follower formation trajectories, thus enhancing cooperative capability. Furthermore, a dual-layer ISMC is proposed, integrating a time-delay compensator for position-attitude synchronization with a robust bounded function for nonlinear terms. In addition, rigorous Lyapunov-based analysis guarantees that the tracking errors are uniformly ultimately bounded. Compared with the extended state observer based ISMC, the proposed ISMC achieves more than 50% reduction in most steady-state errors, while also noticeably improving control input performance.
