TI  - Distributed TMPC formation trajectory tracking of multi-UUV with time-varying communication delay
PY  - 2024
JO  - OCEAN ENGINEERING
DO  - 10.1016/j.oceaneng.2024.117091
AB  - For the problem of multiple underwater unmanned vehicle (UUV) formation control with time-varying communication delays, current interferences, and model uncertainties in marine environments, a distributed tube model prediction controller (DTMPC) based on a double-closed-loop under the communication synchronization strategy is proposed. A state information buffer is first designed to synchronize the asynchronous information with communication delay. Then, the computational complexity is reduced by the double-closed-loop structure with serial control of position and velocity controllers, while the stable convergence of position and velocity is guaranteed, and the problems of current interference and model uncertainty are solved by combining the tube MPC and the extended state observer in the velocity controller. In addition, the feasibility, stability and effectiveness of the formation controller are verified through the stability theorem and simulation experiment. The tracking error of each UUV quickly converges to around zero, and the UUV formation can quickly form a formation and accurately track the target trajectory.
